<section id="shift">
  <title><indexterm significance="normal">
      <primary>shifts</primary>
      <secondary>adding new</secondary>
    </indexterm>Shift</title>
  <para>To add a new Shift to the master list of Shifts, select the NEW
  button. The following screen will appear:</para>
  <para><screenshot>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="images/shift.png" />
        </imageobject>
        <caption>Create New Shift</caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </screenshot></para>
  <para>When adding a new Shift to the master list of Shifts, you are
  presented with the following options:</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Shift Number</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Enter a unique code to identify the Shift.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Shift Name</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Enter a brief name to describe the Shift.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Active</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Check this option if the Shift is active</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Shift Times</term>
      <listitem>
        <variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Shift Start Time</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>Enter the start time for this Shift</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Before Start Rounding</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>Enter the amount of time in minutes that a worker can
              clock in before the Shift start time without adding additional
              time</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>After Start Rounding</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>Enter the amount of time in minutes that a worker can
              clock in after the Shift start time without any time being
              subtracted</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Auto Clock Out Time</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>The time at which a worker will be automatically clocked
              out if not manually clocked out</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Breaks</term>
      <listitem>
        <variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>First Break Start</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>Enter the start time for the first break</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>First Break End</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>Enter the time when the first break is over</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Paid</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>Check this option if the duration of the first break
              should be added to paid time</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Lunch Start</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>Enter the start time for Lunch</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Lunch End</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>Enter the end time for Lunch</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Paid</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>Check this option if the worker receives payment for the
              lunch break<note>
                  <para>If a lunch break is not paid, the system will
                  automatically post a zero value at the end of the lunch
                  break</para>
                </note></para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Second Break Start</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>Enter the start time for the second break in the
              Shift</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Second Break End</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>Enter the end time for the Shift's second break</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Paid</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>Check this option if the duration of the first break
              should be added to paid time</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Employee Information</term>
      <listitem>
        <variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Standard Labor Rate</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>Select the name of the standard labor rate that should be
              applied to this shift. Labor rates are set up in Standard Labor
              Rates under <guimenu>Products &gt; Setup</guimenu></para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Overtime Hours (Weekly)</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>Overtime will be calculated after this amount of hours has
              been allocated according to the standard labor rate</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Overtime Rate Multiplier</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>The standard labor rate selected above will be multiplied
              with this factor</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>Overhead G/L Account</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>Time not associated with a shift will be posted to this
              account</para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
</section>
